<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <title>Grids for Desktop</title>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.3.1/css/bootstrap.min.css">
  <style>
    body {
      background-color: #f2f6ff;
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    }
    .header {
      background-color: #343a40;
      color: white;
      padding: 30px;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .section-title {
      color: #343a40;
      margin-top: 30px;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .grid-box {
      background-color: #ffffff;
      border: 2px solid #343a40;
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      text-align: center;
      font-weight: bold;
      box-shadow: 0px 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
    }
    .grid-box small {
      display: block;
      font-weight: normal;
      margin-top: 8px;
      color: #555;
    }
    .footer {
      background-color: #343a40;
      color: white;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 15px;
      margin-top: 30px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <div class="header">
    <h1>Grids for Desktop</h1>
    <p>Learning how Bootstrap grid looks on a desktop screen!</p>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section-title">Four Equal Boxes</h2>

    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-12 col-lg-3">
        <div class="grid-box">
          Box 1
          <small>On desktop, this takes one-fourth of the row.</small>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="col-12 col-lg-3">
        <div class="grid-box">
          Box 2
          <small>All boxes stay in one line on large screens.</small>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="col-12 col-lg-3">
        <div class="grid-box">
          Box 3
          <small>This makes the page look neat and balanced.</small>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="col-12 col-lg-3">
        <div class="grid-box">
          Box 4
          <small>Bootstrap makes the layout responsive.</small>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="section-title">Main and Side Area</h2>

    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-12 col-lg-8">
        <div class="grid-box">
          Main Section
          <small>This is the larger part of the desktop layout.</small>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
        <div class="grid-box">
          Side Section
          <small>This smaller box is useful for extra information.</small>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="section-title">Three Desktop Columns</h2>

    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
        <div class="grid-box">
          Column A
          <small>Perfect for text, images, or cards.</small>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
        <div class="grid-box">
          Column B
          <small>Each column becomes equal on desktop.</small>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
        <div class="grid-box">
          Column C
          <small>This is a simple way to design webpages.</small>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="footer">
    <p>Made with Bootstrap Grid — Desktop Layout Practice</p>
  </div>

  <script src="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.3.1/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
